page.title: 14Sadie's Day-N.W.Edinburgh
page.content: {A day in the life of Sadie Graham. In the morning Sadie wakes up at 8.00a.m. She does not eat any breakfast but she feeds her daughter. After breakfast she takes her daughter to nursery. When she returns home she does the housework. This describes her {home life. On{Tuesday 21st.May 1985,}Sadie took her daughter to the beach to have a picnic. They drank lemonade and ate sandwiches, crisps and biscuits. Later they watched television and ate supper at about 7.30p.m. Sadie then washed her daughter and put her to bed. Sadie then watched television until between ll.30p.m. and midnight, when she herself went to bed.
